{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services/about/research","content_id":"054ef9e8-83f9-487e-9874-e1b1d2aa7c47","description":"We commission scientific research and development, worth several million pounds a year, to support waste management.","details":{"attachments":[{"accessible":true,"alternative_format_contact_email":"info@nuclearwasteservices.uk","assets":[{"asset_manager_id":"61f25d96d3bf7f78e96049b1","filename":"Science_and_Technology_Plan_2020.pdf"},{"asset_manager_id":"61f25d96e90e07689cd9a936","filename":"thumbnail_Science_and_Technology_Plan_2020.pdf.png"}],"attachment_type":"file","content_type":"application/pdf","file_size":13246932,"filename":"Science_and_Technology_Plan_2020.pdf","id":"8096735","number_of_pages":769,"title":"Science and Technology Plan 2020","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/61f25d96d3bf7f78e96049b1/Science_and_Technology_Plan_2020.pdf"}],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Nuclear Waste Services has responsibility for implementing the government’s policy for delivering a Geological Disposal Facility (GDF) for the UK’s higher activity radioactive wastes.</p>\n\n<p>Details of the expected nature and timing of planned generic research and development activities is outlined in our Science and Technology Plan. By ‘generic’, we mean those activities that can be undertaken without specific knowledge of the eventual host site for the geological disposal facility.</p>\n\n<section data-module=\"ga4-link-tracker\" class=\"gem-c-attachment govuk-!-margin-bottom-6\">\n  <div class=\"gem-c-attachment__thumbnail govuk-!-display-none-print\">\n    <a class=\"govuk-link\" target=\"_self\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-hidden=\"true\" data-ga4-link='{\"event_name\":\"file_download\",\"type\":\"attachment\"}' href=\"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/61f25d96d3bf7f78e96049b1/Science_and_Technology_Plan_2020.pdf\">\n        <svg class=\"gem-c-attachment__thumbnail-image gem-c-attachment__thumbnail-image--pdf\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 99 140\">\n  <path d=\"M12,59h9v9h-9v-9ZM30,77v9h39v-9H30ZM30,104h57v-9H30v9ZM30,122h48v-9H30v9ZM12,86h9v-9h-9v9ZM12,122h9v-9h-9v9ZM12,104h9v-9h-9v9ZM30,68h57v-9H30v9ZM35.2,21c-.3-.2-.6-.4-1-.5s-.8-.2-1.3-.2h-2.6v5.5h2.6c.5,0,1,0,1.3-.2s.7-.3,1-.5c.3-.2.5-.5.7-.8s.2-.7.2-1.1h0c0-.5,0-.9-.2-1.2-.2-.3-.4-.6-.7-.8h0ZM52.4,21.9c-.4-.5-1-.9-1.6-1.1-.7-.3-1.5-.4-2.4-.4h-2.7v11.5h2.7c.9,0,1.7-.1,2.4-.4s1.2-.7,1.6-1.1c.4-.5.7-1.1.9-1.7.2-.7.3-1.4.3-2.1v-.7c0-.8,0-1.5-.3-2.1-.2-.6-.5-1.2-.9-1.7h0ZM87,12v27H12V12h75ZM39.8,23c0-.9-.1-1.6-.4-2.4-.3-.7-.7-1.4-1.2-1.9-.5-.5-1.2-1-1.9-1.2-.8-.3-1.6-.5-2.5-.5h-7.2v17.9h3.6v-6h3.2c.9,0,1.8-.1,2.6-.5.8-.3,1.4-.7,2-1.2.5-.5,1-1.2,1.3-1.9.3-.7.5-1.5.5-2.4h0ZM57.4,26c0-1.3-.2-2.6-.5-3.7s-.9-2-1.6-2.8c-.7-.8-1.6-1.4-2.7-1.8-1.1-.4-2.3-.6-3.8-.6h-6.6v17.9h6.6c1.5,0,2.7-.2,3.8-.6,1.1-.4,2-1,2.7-1.8.7-.8,1.3-1.7,1.6-2.8.4-1.1.5-2.3.5-3.7h0ZM72.4,17.1h-12.1v17.9h3.6v-7.5h7.8v-3.3h-7.8v-3.8h8.4s0-3.3,0-3.3Z\"></path>\n</svg>\n\n</a>\n</div>\n  <div class=\"gem-c-attachment__details\">\n    <h2 class=\"gem-c-attachment__title\">\n      <a class=\"govuk-link\" target=\"_self\" data-ga4-link='{\"event_name\":\"file_download\",\"type\":\"attachment\"}' href=\"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/61f25d96d3bf7f78e96049b1/Science_and_Technology_Plan_2020.pdf\">Science and Technology Plan 2020</a>\n</h2>\n\n\n      <p class=\"gem-c-attachment__metadata\"><span class=\"gem-c-attachment__attribute\"><abbr title=\"Portable Document Format\" class=\"gem-c-attachment__abbr\">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class=\"gem-c-attachment__attribute\">12.6 MB</span>, <span class=\"gem-c-attachment__attribute\">769 pages</span></p>\n\n\n\n\n</div></section>\n\n<p>As a subsidiary of the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority, Nuclear Waste Services also participates in NDA’s Research and Development Programme.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority/about/research\" class=\"govuk-link\">Find out more about Research at NDA</a></p>\n\n<h2 id=\"research-support-office\">Research Support Office</h2>\n\n<p>Our Research Support Office aims to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>deliver academic research outputs that align closely with Nuclear Waste Services’ needs</li>\n  <li>centrally manage research, delivering more coordinated and targeted research</li>\n  <li>improve contextual understanding and engagement</li>\n  <li>capitalise on economic opportunities from universities and other funding bodies to drive forward research</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Research teams within our partner universities benefit from funding that enables them to develop the next generation of researchers. This community of scientists will have specialised knowledge of geological disposal of radioactive waste and the social issues that surround it. Having this knowledge and expertise coordinated across the UK’s academic institutions allows regulators and supply chain companies to tap into the latest research to inform their strategies.</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.research-support-office-gdf.ac.uk/\" class=\"govuk-link\">Research Support Office website</a></p>\n\n<h2 id=\"technical-publications-related-to-geological-disposal\">Technical Publications related to Geological Disposal</h2>\n\n<p>An archive of previously published technical publications can be found by <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/search/\" class=\"govuk-link\">searching the National Archive</a>.</p>\n\n<p>These 2 documents provide a list of publications related to Geological Disposal. Links are provided where downloadable versions are available in the National Web Archive:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gdf-bibliography-summary-1983-to-2007\" class=\"govuk-link\">GDF Bibliography Summary 1983 to 2007</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gdf-bibliography-summary-2007-to-2021\" class=\"govuk-link\">GDF Bibliography Summary 2007 to 2021</a></p>\n\n<p>Technical publications are now published within the research section of GOV.UK to give people the opportunity to understand progress on various scientific and technical issues related to managing nuclear waste and geological disposal.</p>\n\n<p>For further information, please see <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/search/research-and-statistics?content_store_document_type=research&amp;organisations%5B%5D=committee-on-radioactive-waste-management&amp;organisations%5B%5D=nuclear-decommissioning-authority&amp;organisations%5B%5D=nuclear-waste-services&amp;organisations%5B%5D=radioactive-waste-management&amp;order=updated-newest\" class=\"govuk-link\">Research and statistics - GOV.UK</a> or contact <a href=\"mailto:info@nuclearwasteservices.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\">info@nuclearwasteservices.uk</a></p>\n\n<h2 id=\"issues-register\">Issues Register</h2>\n\n<p>Activity to resolve issues previously raised through RWM’s Issues Register are included in the Science and Technology Plan. Engagement with stakeholders on various issues continues through various channels. An <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/ukgwa/20200703231454/https:/rwm.nda.gov.uk/issues/\" class=\"govuk-link\">archive of the Issues Register webpages can be found in via The National Web Archives.</a></p>\n\n<p>Since launching the Issues Management process, other channels and engagement opportunities have been put in place for stakeholders to raise queries and understand progress on various scientific and technical issues related to geological disposal.</p>\n\n<p>For further information, please explore Nuclear Waste Services’ website or contact <a href=\"mailto:info@nuclearwasteservices.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\">info@nuclearwasteservices.uk</a></p>\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"Updated to reflect Nuclear Waste Services becoming a single legal entity and updated email address for contacting NWS.","public_timestamp":"2024-07-24T11:24:27Z"},{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2022-01-31T08:00:04Z"}],"headers":[{"id":"research-support-office","level":2,"text":"Research Support Office"},{"id":"technical-publications-related-to-geological-disposal","level":2,"text":"Technical Publications related to Geological Disposal"},{"id":"issues-register","level":2,"text":"Issues Register"}],"organisation":"87ad1f5a-f535-433c-8dde-eae033c593ec","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"research","first_published_at":"2022-01-31T08:00:06+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services/about/research","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services/about/research","base_path":"/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services/about/research","content_id":"054ef9e8-83f9-487e-9874-e1b1d2aa7c47","document_type":"research","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-07-24T11:24:27Z","schema_name":"corporate_information_page","title":"Research at Nuclear Waste Services","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services/about/research","withdrawn":false}],"organisations":[{"analytics_identifier":"OT1347","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services","base_path":"/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services","content_id":"87ad1f5a-f535-433c-8dde-eae033c593ec","details":{"acronym":"","brand":"department-for-business-innovation-skills","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/61f410f08fa8f5388e978131/s960_NWS_RGB_Full_Name_Logo_White960x640.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/61f410f18fa8f538921d1e2d/s300_NWS_RGB_Full_Name_Logo_White960x640.jpg"},"logo":{"crest":"custom","formatted_title":"Nuclear Waste Services","image":{"alt_text":"Nuclear Waste Servi